Issues.Body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
As a now, while navigating through Keyboard that focus is not clearly visible on "Categorized", "Alphabetical" and " Property Pages". As a result, it is difficult for people with vision problems to use these buttons. As #3659 suggested, a dotted border for these buttons would make it easier for the user to work with this control
![3659-issue](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/23376742/95464038-2e2c8480-0982-11eb-8e8b-f26176e069db.gif)

**Describe the solution you'd like and alternatives you've considered**
Add the dotted border for ToolStripButton

API:
```
public class ToolStripButtonBorderRenderEventArgs : ToolStripItemRenderEventArgs
{
    /// <summary>
    /// This class represents all the information to render the ToolStrip
    /// </summary>
    public ToolStripButtonBorderRenderEventArgs(Graphics g,
                                                ToolStripItem item,
                                                Rectangle borderRectangle,
                                                Color borderColor,
                                                int borderWidth,
                                                ButtonBorderStyle buttonBorderStyle) : base(g, item)
    {
        if (item is null)
        {
            throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(item));
        }

        BorderWidth = borderWidth;
        BorderColor = borderColor;
        BorderRectangle = borderRectangle;
        ButtonBorderStyle = buttonBorderStyle;
    }

    ///  The color of border
    internal Color BorderColor { get; set; }

    /// <summary>
    ///  The width of border
    /// </summary>
    public int BorderWidth { get; set; }

    /// <summary>
    ///  The rectangle to draw the border
    /// </summary>
    public Rectangle BorderRectangle { get; set; }

    /// <summary>
    ///  The border style
    /// </summary>
    public ButtonBorderStyle ButtonBorderStyle { get; set; }
}
```
and new methods in ToolStripRender:
```
public event EventHandler<ToolStripButtonBorderRenderEventArgs> RenderButtonBorder
{
    add => AddHandler(EventRenderButtonBorder, value);
    remove => RemoveHandler(EventRenderButtonBorder, value);
}

public void DrawButtonBorder(ToolStripButtonBorderRenderEventArgs e)

protected virtual void OnRenderButtonBorder(ToolStripButtonBorderRenderEventArgs e)

```
This API is suggested in line with the API of other methods in ToolStripRender class and will be used in `ToolStripButton.OnPaint` method:
```
if (Selected)
{
    renderer.DrawButtonBorder(new ToolStripButtonBorderRenderEventArgs(e.Graphics, this, ClientBounds, Color.Black, 1, ButtonBorderStyle.Dotted));
}
```
An excellent visualization of what this might look like after fixing:
![3659-fixed](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/23376742/95464731-f70aa300-0982-11eb-9ed5-a9bb08d8808c.gif)

**Will this feature affect UI controls?**
Yes.

**Will VS Designer need to support the feature?**
It would be nice to use this to PropertyGrid in VS

**What impact will it have on accessibility?**
This will make it easier for people with vision problems to use this control.

**Will this feature need to be localized or be localizable?**
This feature does not need localization
